hdDGdaTeneok","target":"reck1tM8WWYzlqojS","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rece7hdDGdaTeneok","target":"recSP9AgOTeRwE28z","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rece7hdDGdaTeneok","target":"recLFwe2uKBqJwmWn","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rece7hdDGdaTeneok","target":"recBYO9ocr5Gssb47","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rece7hdDGdaTeneok","target":"recly2TmP9CBHh8OQ","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"reczffIIG1JpN2VRn","ref":"1Tim.1.1","text":"Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the commandment of God our Saviour, and Lord Jesus Christ, which is our hope;","year":65},{"id":"rec1XHrikq2uuLDq4","ref":"1Tim.1.2","text":"Unto Timothy, my own son in the faith: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God our Father and Jesus Christ our Lord.","year":65},{"id":"recFREqH0f2EcKrCQ","ref":"1Tim.1.3","text":"As I besought thee to abide still at Ephesus, when I went into Macedonia, that thou mightest charge some that they teach no other doctrine,","year":65},{"id":"rechV7oRW0W8L7MkT","ref":"1Tim.1.4","text":"Neither give heed to fables and endless genealogies, which minister questions, rather than godly edifying which is in faith: so do.","year":65},{"id":"rec4JMSn7Qhav53Da","ref":"1Tim.1.5","text":"Now the end of the commandment is charity out of a pure heart, and of a good conscience, and of faith unfeigned:","year":65},{"id":"reckh96q50Ckdwkvp","ref":"1Tim.1.6","text":"From which some having swerved have turned aside unto vain jangling;","year":65},{"id":"recAREKBJzazptUGv","ref":"1Tim.1.7","text":"Desiring to be teachers of the law; understanding neither what they say, nor whereof they affirm.","year":65},{"id":"reclRMgbm6UhLYXRF","ref":"1Tim.1.8","text":"But we know that the law is good, if a man use it lawfully;","year":65}]}
